entry.title: Migrant Influx Overwhelms Southern Border as Title 42 Winds Down
entry.content: A massive surge of migrants sought to cross from Mexico into the U.S., straining resources and patience on both sides of the border as the pandemic-era measure known as Title 42 was set to end at midnight.
